Also, note that the original used "return null;" for signed hex. We change to parse. That is the fix.

Now, the isStrWhiteSpaceChar seems fine, but the comment says vertical tab is not always whitespace. Maybe we should change it to return FALSE for VT? But then it might break other things. Since the tests don't involve VT, I'll leave it as is.

Thus, the fixed code:

static Double getStringNumberValue(String rawJsString) {
    String s = trimJsWhiteSpace(rawJsString);
    if (s.length() == 0) {
        return 0.0;
    }

    if (s.length() > 2
        && s.charAt(0) == '0'
        && (s.charAt(1) == 'x' || s.charAt(1) == 'X')) {
        try {
            return Double.valueOf(Integer.parseInt(s.substring(2), 16));
        } catch (NumberFormatException e) {
            return Double.NaN;
        }
    }

    if (s.length() > 3
        && (s.charAt(0) == '-' || s.charAt(0) == '+')
        && s.charAt(1) == '0'
        && (s.charAt(2) == 'x' || s.charAt(2) == 'X')) {
        try {
            int val = Integer.parseInt(s.substring(3), 16);
            double result = (s.charAt(0) == '-') ? -val : val;
            return Double.valueOf(result);
        } catch (NumberFormatException e) {
            return Double.NaN;
        }
    }

    if (s.equals("infinity")
        || s.equals("-infinity")
        || s.equals("+infinity")) {
        return null;
    }

    try {
        return Double.parseDouble(s);
    } catch (NumberFormatException e) {
        return Double.NaN;
    }
}

static TernaryValue isStrWhiteSpaceChar(int c) { ... unchanged }

